{
  "stem": "20089.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So in my usual, very intensive way, I started reading about Jewish history and Jewish culture, and realized that anti-semitism is something that one should be very much aware of, and that the fact that I worked in the camps was a result of anti-semite-- anti-semitic views that were held in Europe pre-war, and probably centuries old.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I became very, very Jewish-orientated-- not religious, but very Jewish-orientated.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I started collecting all the literature and all the books that were written about the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And now I have an enormous library of Holocaust literature.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think that my first-- the first thing that I think struck me was there but for the grace of God could I have been.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If we left in 1929, it was really just far-- '29, '39-- about 12 years before the onset of the war, or 10 years, really. 10 years, because the war started in '39.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was 10 years before the onset of the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I really escaped by virtue of the fact that my parents-- my father, particularly-- had the foresight to leave Europe.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And in a way, I felt, I suppose, guilty that I had survived when so many of my family did not survive.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father's family were all wiped out, except for one cousin in Warsaw that I visit regularly.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My mother's family survived in greater numbers, although most of them were in concentration camps or in orphanages during the war.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when I re-met them in Europe, as I did, I think it must have had some kind of impact.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They are survivors and these are their experiences.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you didn't really identify with them when you were in-- in Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You felt almost alienated to them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then suddenly, that alienation just disappeared.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
